HarvEast, a Ukrainian agricultural
holding company formed by Rinat Akhmetov and Vadim Novinsky,
said it may build a grain elevator in the Donetsk region.  The company is now developing a project to build a 100,000
ton one-time capacity, the company, which is based in Donetsk,
in the eastern part of Ukraine, said in e-mailed statement
today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
